 (10,1,'c','print preview is for setting up or adjusting pages to be printed\r\nit has five submenu.\r\nI)print(print, options)\r\nII)page setup (margin,orientation,size)\r\nIII)zoom,\r\nIV) preview(show ruler,magnifier,shrink pages,close print preview)\r\n','154','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (11,1,'a','COMPUTER IS AN ELECTRONIC DATA PROCESSING DEVICE THAT TAKES INPUT FROM THE USERS, PROCESSES IT AS PER THE USER REPUIREMENTS AND GIVES THE REPURED RESULTS.\r\nTHE BLOCK DIAGRAM OF THE COMPUTER CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING UNTIS\r\n1) INPUT UNIT\r\n2) PROCESSING UNIT\r\n3) OUTPUT UNIT\r\n\r\n1) INPUT UNIT: THIS UNIT RECEIVES THE INFO/DATA FROM THE USER AND GIVES THE PROCESSING SECTION/ CPU. \r\nEG: KEYBOARD, MOUSE, JOYSTICK ETC\r\n2)PROCESSING UNIT: THIS UNIT CONSISTS OF THE ALU, CU, MEMORY UNTIS ETC\r\nALU PERFORMS ARITHMATIC AND LOGICAL OPERETIONS\r\nCU PERFORMS CONTROLLING OPERATIONS\r\nMEMORY UNIT HAS HARD DISK, RAM, ROM, REGISTER & CACHE MEMORIESETC.\r\n3) OUTPUT UNIT: GIVES THE DESIRED OUTPUT\r\nEG: MONITER, SPEAKER, PRINTER ETC.','126','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
