 (22,1,'A','','154','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (23,1,'a','Block diagram of computer consists of 3 main parts. They are-\r\n(1) Input unit: It receives inputs like data, numbers,etc from the user. Examples for input unit are- keyboard, mouse,scanner,etc.\r\n(2) Processing unit: It processes the data from the input devices.This unit is composed of CPU. The CPU in turn consists of AIRTHMETIC AND LOGIC UNIT(ALU) and CONTROL UNIT. ALU performs the logical ','143','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (24,1,'a','Input:Through which input can be given to CPU.eg:keyboard,mouse\r\n \r\nOutput:whatever data given to computer processed and it will give result as output.output devices eg:printer,monitor\r\n\r\nCentral Processing Unit(CPU)\r\na)Arthmatic And logic Unit(ALU):It will compute the data arthmatic and logic function and give result to output devices\r\nb)Memory Unit:It will store the data,both to and fro whatever the data computed it will store in the memry and whenever required we can access from memory any time\r\n\r\n\r\n','128','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (25,1,'a','computer consists of following blocks.\r\n1)Input devices: This block is used to feed the input data into the computer. Examples: keyboard, mouse, microphone etc.\r\n2)Output devices: This block is used to display the processed data i.e output or result. Examples: printer, monitor, loud speakers etc.\r\n3)Airthmatic logic unit : This  block is used to perform airthmatic and logic functions like addition, substraction, multiplication etc.\r\n4)Memory unit: This unit used to store the data.\r\n 2 types in memory a)primary memory b)secondary memory\r\n5)Control unit : To control the system to perform different work and it is called brain of the memory.\r\n  \r\n','127','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (26,1,'a','Block diagram consist of 3 parts that are Input, Processing unit and Output. Input devices are keyboard, Scanner etc devices takes the inputs and gives to the processing unit. Processing unit consists storage and CPU units. CPU work is process the data and sends to storage unit and it passes to cpu and then passes to the output unit. Output units are monitor and speakers etc   ','156','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (27,1,'a','computer is a mechanical device which performs the task given by the users. the tasks mainly done by programs in the computer. computer consists of two main parts they are\r\n1.hardware \r\n2.software\r\nthe block diagram of computer (hardware) three main components they are\r\n1.central processing unit \r\n2.control unit\r\n3.arithmetic and logic unit\r\nCPU or central processing unit mainly processes any data which means according to the programs and input given it perform the operation.\r\ncpu also fetches data from the hard ware device and also stores the results it communicates with the control unit and alu\r\n2.arithmetic logic units does all the operation requested by cpu like arithmetic and logical operation\r\n3.control unit is brain of the computer it decides  what to do next and it convers between CPU and ALU.  ','135','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (28,1,'a','Block diagram of computer consists of\r\na)Input device\r\nb)CPU\r\nc)Output device\r\nInput devices are used to provide inputs to the processor to perform various operations. Example-mouse, keyboard, scanner\r\nCPU consists of control unit, memory registers and ALU\r\nControl unit is called the heart of the CPU. It is used to control the functioning of ALU.\r\nMemory are used to store the data processed from ALU.Various types of memory are temporary and permanent memory.Random access memory and read only memory.Various storage devices used are cd,dvd,pendrives,Floppy disks.\r\nMemory used in the computer ranges from Kilobytes to Terabytes range.\r\n1byte=8bits\r\n1kilobyte=1024bytes\r\nOutput devices are used to output the processed data.Various output devices are monitor,Printer.','149','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (29,1,'A','COMPUTER CONSISTS MAILY FOUR PARTS NAMELY \r\n1)MONITOR\r\n2)KEYBOARD\r\n3)CPU\r\n4)MOUSE\r\n1)MONITOR :MONITOR IS A OUTPUT DEVICE WHICH DISPLAYS THE RESULTS WHICH HAVE BEEN CARRIED OUT BY CPU ON THE BASIS OF INPUT GIVEN BY USER.\r\n2)KEYBOARD : KEYBOARD IS AN INPUT DEVICE USED TO GIVE INSTRUCTIONS LIKE ALPHABET , NUMERIC , AND SPECIAL CHARECTERS TO THE COMPUTER.\r\n3) CPU : CPU STANDS FOR CENTRAL PROCESSING UNIT.IT IS A MAIN PART OF THE COMPUTER.IT CONSISTS OF ALU,MEMORY UNITS, CONTROL UNITS ETC.IT PERFORMS ALL OPERATIONS ACCORDING TO INPUT INSTRUCTIONS.\r\n4) MOUSE : INPUT DEVICE USED TO CONTROL THE CURSOR MOVEMENTS ON THE SCREEN AND SELECTING,OPENING THE PERTICULAR FILES OR FOLDERS.  \r\n\r\n','147','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (30,1,'a','computer is an electronic device, it can perform operations based on the input what we enter in a short interval of time,without error.\r\nIt can be hardly divided into two types:\r\n1)hardware\r\n2)software\r\n1)Hardware: The things what we seen by naked eyes and experience their touch are called hardware.\r\nExample:Key board,mouse etc...\r\n2)software  : The programed instructions to perform a particular task is called as safware.\r\nExample: MS word , MS Exel etc...\r\n\r\nCPU is called as the brain of computer.\r\na)airthmatic and logic unit(ALU)  :this unit performs the mathematical and logical operations.\r\nb)computer is an electronic device, it can perform operations based on the input what we enter in a short interval of time,without error.\r\nIt can be hardly divided into two types:\r\n1)hardware\r\n2)software\r\n1)Hardware: The things what we seen by naked eyes and experience their touch are called hardware.\r\nExample:Key board,mouse etc...\r\n2)software  : The programed instructions to perform a particular task is called as safware.\r\nExample: MS word , MS Exel etc...\r\n\r\nCPU is called as the brain of computer.\r\na)airthmatic and logic unit(ALU)  :this unit performs the mathematical and logical operations.\r\nb)control unit: it control the performance of the computer.\r\nc)memory unit:this unit stores the contents what we excecute in the system and store in it.','136','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (33,1,'a','Block diagram of computer is consist of three main parts \r\n1.Control unit \r\n2.Arthamatic logic unit\r\n3.memory unit.\r\n\r\nControl unit: Control is called as brain of the computer. It control the all activities of the computer. and also it receive the input and analyse the input information and give the output.\r\n\r\nAsthmatic logic unit: it is used to calculate the all mathematic problems.\r\n\r\nMemory unit: It is used to save the data it comes from the control unit and ALU result or output.     ','141','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
