INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (48,1,'a','BLOCK DIAGRAM OF COMPUTER\r\n1.INPUT\r\n2.CPU\r\n3.OUTPUT \r\n1.INPUT : It is an device to give any information to the computer\r\n2.CONTROL PROCESSING UNIT\r\na.MEMORY UNIT :it stored information or mathematical operationin memory\r\nb.CONTROL UNIT :It control the all part of the computer, it is an brain of computer.\r\nc.ARTHMATIC LOGICAL UNIT : It an calculating part of computer\r\n3.OUTPUT :It is an device to give information to an user','139','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (49,1,'c','This option helps to preview the document before printing it. we can change the dimensions and zoom size of a document here. this option includes 1)page setup- margins, orientation size\r\n2)orientation-to switch the page between portrait and landscape\r\n3)paper size','132','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (50,1,'bb','Home Menu\r\n1)Clip board\r\na)cut-It cuts the selected text ctrl+x\r\nb)copy-it copied the selected text which we pasted required places ctrl+c\r\nc)paste-It pasted the cut or copied text to pasted required places\r\nctrl+v\r\n2)Font-it changes the font styles of the selected text which we wanted\r\n it can changes the font face font size increase and decrease the font it bolds underlined itealised the word. it makes the word looks like a marked with high lighten colour','144','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (51,1,'a','Block diagram of computer mainly contains three parts.\r\n1)INPUT\r\n2)CPU\r\n3)OUTPUT\r\nINPUT-Input means this is what we gave instruction to the computer or what we gave the data to do work to the computer.\r\nCPU- central processing unit which is called as heart of the computer. which contain mainly three parts.\r\n1)memory unit-This is called as brain of the computer. which save the data. this have primary memory and secondary memory two types of memory.\r\n2)al u unit- Airthmatic and logic unit which perform the airthmatical operation and also the logical operations.\r\n3)control unit- which control the process of the computer operations.\r\nOUTPUT- Output means that what we given work to the computer which perform operations and it give the result as outout.\r\nthis is brief explaination about the block diagaram of the computer.','145','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (54,1,'c','Print preview:\r\n1.Print\r\n a.Print:(Ctrl+P)->used to print the current page.\r\n b.Options:->Used to change the printing options of current page.\r\n2.Page set up:\r\n 1.Margin:->Used to change the margin of page.\r\n 2.Orientation->used to change the orientation as partrait and landscape.\r\n 3.size->Used to change the the size of page as A4,A3 etc\r\nc.Zoom->used to check the zoom level of printing document.\r\n','160','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (55,1,'aa','functions. The CONTROL UNIT(CU) is a component of the CPU, and it controlls the computers memeory, I/p, o/p devoces.\r\nThird part of computer is - OUTPUT UNIT- It displays the processed data on the o/p devices like montor, plotter,etc.','143','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (56,1,'b','HOME:\r\nCLIPBOARD:\r\n CUT: This option is used to cut the selected text from the document.\r\n COPY: This option is used to copy the selected text from the document.\r\n PASTE: This option is used to paste copied data to specific selected file or folder.\r\nfonts:\r\n    BOLD :  This option is used to bold the letters in given paragraphUnderline : This option is used to made  underline below the selected word.\r\n \r\n Subscript : This option is used create small letters below  the selected words.\r\n Super script :  This option is used to create small letters above the selected words.\r\n  Grow font :  This option is option is used incense the size of font from low to high.\r\n  Shrink font : This option is used to decrees the size of font from high to low.\r\n  Text highlight cover : This key is used to highlight the selected paragraph line with selected colour.\r\n  Font size : This key has option to decrees or increase the size of letter. \r\n PARAGRAPH.\r\n  Bullets : This option is used made bullet marks to write data in order.\r\n Numbering : This option is used to made numbers in columns.\r\n  Right align text: This option is used to move selected lines of paragraph to right.\r\n Left align text : This option is used to move selected lines of paragraph to left.\r\n LINE SPACING : This option is used to maintain the space between lines in a paragraph.\r\n  SHADING : This option is used to highlights the selected text in a paragraph.\r\n  BOARDER : This option is used to draw border lines left,right,bottam and top of the selected text.\r\n SORT : This option is used to sort the text in a ascending or descending order. \r\n  INCRESE INDENT : This option is used to move the indent in word document to right. \r\n  INCRESE INDENT : This option is used to move the indent in word document to right. \r\n \r\n \r\n','136','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (58,1,'a','Computer:Computer is an electronic device. It takes the data and give it in the form of information.\r\nInput unit:It gives rough data to the computer.\r\nCPU: It is called Brain of computer. It manages the control unit and memory unit.\r\nALU:It performs arithmetical and logical operations.\r\nControl unit: It controls all the operations of Computer.\r\nMemory unit:It stores the data. There are two types of Memories 1)Primary memory. 2)Secondary memory.\r\nOutput unit:It takes the data and give it in the form of information.\r\n ','130','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (59,1,'a','Computer is a Electronics Device. It consists of INPUT,CPU,OUTPUT\r\nINPUT- It give input to the device. example keyboard, mouse, microphone,  joystick, touch pad stick, etc\r\nCPU(central processing unit)-It is a Brain of the computer.It is a processing part it consists of ALU(Arithmetic logical Unit),Memory unit. ALU is perform Arithmetic logical operation and all logical operation. Memory Unit consists of RAM ,ROM, Cache Memory, Hard Dick. after operation save the data in Hard dick. it is permanent. fastest memory is cache memory. \r\nOUTPUT Unit- It is out to device .The fetched data to show.  Example monitor, printer, plotter .','161','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (62,1,'b','Home menu options given below:\r\n1)Clip board \r\na)Copy: ctrl+c ,To copy the selected item in the document.\r\nb)Cut : ctrl+x ,To cut the selected content in the document.\r\nc)Paste: ctrl+p , To paste the selected item in the document.\r\n\r\n2)FONT :\r\na)Font: Shift+ctrl+F\r\n  To choose different font .\r\nb)Font size: Shift+ctrl+P\r\n To change the size of the selected text in the documents. \r\nc)Font type: To change the font types.\r\n   There 3 types *Bold -cntrl+B\r\n                 *Italic-cntrl+I\r\n                 *Underline-cntrl+U \r\nd)Change case:Change all selected text to upper case, lower case, sentence case etc.\r\ne)Subscript and superscript: To create small letters below and above the baseline.\r\nf)Strike through: Draw the line through middle of the word.\r\ng)Text highlight colour: To marked the selected text.\r\nh)Font colour: To change text colour.\r\n','127','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (63,1,'e','print preview:\r\n\r\nprint: to print through printer or to set options of printing\r\npage setup: to adjust margins, orientations such as landscape or portrait, or to adjust the size of the print layout.\r\nzoomin options are used to display the text is required size and to view 2 or 3 pages at a time etc\r\npreview menu has options to preview, options to toggle through pages etc.','126','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
