 (64,1,'b','Home menu mainly contains clipboard, Font, Paragraph and style sub menu. \r\n\r\n\r\nClip Board\r\n \r\n1.Cut - ctrl+x\r\nIt Cut(remove  and placed in clipboard)  the selected character.\r\n \r\n\r\n2.Copy - Ctrl+c\r\nClip board keeps the copy of selected characters.\r\n \r\n3.Paste - ctrl+v\r\nPaste the characters which are hold in clipboard.\r\n \r\n\r\n4.Format painter - Ctrl+Shift+c\r\nIt just copy the format of selected character.\r\n \r\n\r\nII.Font\r\n1.Style \r\nUsing this option we can select the character style.\r\nEg:- Calibri, Times New Roman, CAsteller\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n2.Size - ctrl+[  /  ctrl+]\r\nWe can Increase and decrease the character size as per our requirement .\r\nEg:-Police Training College\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n3.Bold  -  ctrl+b\r\nWhich will make the selected characters in to Bold letters.\r\nEg:-Police Training College\r\n \r\n\r\n4.Italic  -  ctrl+I\r\nItalicize the selected texts.\r\nEg:-Police Training College\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n5.Under Line - ctrl+u\r\nIt under line the selected texts.\r\nEg:- Police Training College\r\n \r\n\r\n6.Strike\r\nDraw the line through middle of the text.\r\nEg:- Police Training College\r\n \r\n\r\n7.Sub script - ctrl+=\r\nWrite the small text below right side of the baseline.\r\nEg:- H2O \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n8.Super script - ctrl+shift+=\r\nWrite the small text below right side of the baseline.\r\nEg:- 102\r\n \r\n\r\n9.Change case - Shift+F3\r\na.Lower Case\r\nChange the selected texts in to lowercase letters.\r\nEg:- police training college\r\nb.Upper case \r\nChange the selected texts in to uppercase letters.\r\nEg:- POLICE TRAINING COLLEGE\r\nc.Sentence case\r\nCapitalize the first letter of the Sentence.\r\nEg:-  Police training college.\r\nd.Capitalized each Word\r\n2.Capitalize the first letter of the each word.\r\n3.Eg:-  Police Training College.\r\n\r\na.Toggle case \r\n\r\n \r\n1.Grow Font - ctrl+[  \r\n \r\n\r\n2.Shrink Font -  ctrl+]\r\n \r\n3.Clear Format\r\n \r\n4.Text Highlighter\r\n \r\n\r\n5.Text colour\r\n \r\n\r\nIII.  Paragraph \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n1.Bullets\r\nh \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n2.Numbering\r\n \r\n3.Multi level List\r\n \r\n4.Indent\r\n   Decrease Indent\r\n \r\nIncrease Indent\r\n \r\n5.Sort\r\n \r\n6.Show/Hidden format symbol \r\n \r\n7.Alignment\r\n  Left\r\n \r\nCentre  \r\n \r\n\r\nRight\r\n \r\nJustify\r\n \r\n8.Spacing \r\n','155','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (65,1,'C','&#61692;PRINT : This option is used to print ready word  document. . Shortcut key is cntl+p. \r\n  &#61692;PRINT : This option is used to select a printer , number of copies etc.\r\n &#61692;QUICK PRINT : This option is used to send the document  to the default printer without changes.\r\n &#61692;PRINT PREVIEW : This option is used to preview and make changes  NUMBER OF COPIES. Using this option we add how many numbers of  copies should be printed.\r\n before print.\r\n   COLLATE. This option is used to which page is to print multiple times.\r\n   PAGES. This option is used to what number of pages should print.\r\nEx. 1-6.\r\n ) PAGE SETUP .\r\n\r\ni.MARGINS: provides margin size for the document or selected portion.\r\n  ii.ORIENTATION: Used to switch pages. between portrait and landscape\r\n  iii.SIZE: Used to provide paper size for current section.\r\n ZOOM:\r\nONE PAGE: Zoom the document so that entire page fits the window.ed to \r\nspecify the zoom level of the document.\r\n   iii.TWO PAGES: zooms the document so that two pages fit the window.\r\n iv.PAGE WIDTH: zooms such that width of the page matches the width of the window.\r\ni.SHOW RULER: Helps to view the ruler used in alignment\r\n  ii.MAGNIFIER: Helps to toggle between 100% and fit whole page zoom automatically. \r\n  iii.SHRINK ONE PAGE: Attempts to shrink the document by one page .reducing the size and spacing between words.\r\n  iv.NEXT PAGE: Navigate to next page of the document. \r\n v.PREVIOUS PAGE: Navigate to previous page of the document.\r\n  vi.CLOSE PRINT PREVIEW: close the print preview and return to the editing document.\r\n   \r\n','136','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (67,1,'b','Home option in the Microsoft word applications consists of the following sub menus.\r\n1.clip board\r\na.Cut (ctrl+X)- To Select pertinently an option. \r\nb.Copy (Ctrl+C)- to copy the duplicate copy of the any subject or option.\r\nc.Paste (Ctrl+V)- copied or cut object is pasting in required places\r\nd.Format printer (ctrl+shift+c)-copy formatting from one place and apply it to another.\r\n\r\n2.Font:font options are used to font size, style, bold, italic, and to strike through the selected text in the documents.\r\nand also to make the selected text to subscript, superscript, text highlight colour and change case.\r\n3.Paragraph:it is used to edit the paragraph of the document.\r\n and consists of following options to do edit the paragraph.\r\n bullets, numbering,  decrease indent ,increase indent, multilevel  list, sort option, align text right, align text left, centre and justify options to create the systematic paragraph.\r\n\r\n4.Styles\r\n Style sub menu is used to make different font style in the text or paragraph, they are as given below.\r\na.Normal b.No spacing c.Heading 1  d.Heading 2\r\ne.Title  f.Subtitle   g.Emphasis   and h.Change style -set of change of styles ,colours and fonts used in this particular document.\r\n\r\n5.Editing\r\na.Find-to find the text in document\r\nb.Replace- (ctrl+H) use  to replace the text in documents\r\nc.Select-to select the text or object in the documents.\r\n','137','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (69,1,'b','HOME MENU OPTIONS CONSISTS:-\r\nCLIPBOARD\r\n1)paste\r\n2)copy\r\n3)cut\r\nFONT\r\n4)bold\r\n5)italic\r\n6)underline\r\n7)subscript\r\n8)superscript\r\n9)change case \r\n10)font color \r\n11)grow font\r\n12)shrink font\r\nPARAGRAPH\r\n1)bullets\r\n2)numbering\r\n3)multi level list\r\n4)justify\r\n5)canter\r\nSTYLES\r\n1)emphasis\r\n2)subtitle\r\n3)change style\r\nEDITING\r\n1)find \r\n2)replace \r\n3)select','138','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
