 (70,1,'c','tPrint preview option\r\n\r\n Page setup\r\n\r\nMargins: select the margin sizes for entire  document.\r\norientation:\r\n      a)portrait:the page fits vertically\r\n \r\n      b)landscape:the page fits horizontally.\r\nsize: it selects the size of the paper to get print out.like A3,A4... etc., \r\nzoom: open the zoom dialog box to specify the zoom level of the document\r\n page width : zoom the document so that the width of the document matches with the width of the window.\r\nshow rules :view he rules of the page to print.\r\n\r\n','146','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (71,1,'b','Home menu\r\n \r\n1)Clipboard\r\ni)Cut: (ctl+X), Cut the selection from the document and put it on the clipboard \r\n \r\nii)Copy: (ctl+C) , Copy the selection from the document and put it on the clipboard\r\n \r\niii)Paste :( ctl+V), Paste the selection from the document and put it on the clipboard.\r\n \r\niv)Select all: (ctl+A), we can select the text.\r\nv)Format painter: (ctl+shift+c) Copy formatting from one place and apply it to another.\r\n \r\n2)Font\r\ni)Style: We can change the font style to the selected text. \r\n \r\nii)Size: (ctl+shift+P) we can change the font size to the selected text.\r\n \r\niii)Colour: We can change the font colour to the selected text.\r\n \r\niv)Underline: We can give the Underline to the selected text.\r\n \r\nv)Bold: We can make Bold to the selected text.\r\n \r\nvi)Italic: We can make Italic to the selected text.\r\n \r\nvii)Strike through: We can do the strike through to the selected text. \r\n \r\nviii)Super script: We can do the Super script to the selected text.\r\n \r\nix)Sub script: We can do the Sub script to the selected text.\r\n \r\n3)Paragraph\r\ni)Left alignment :( ctl+L) we can make left alignment to the selected text.\r\n \r\nii)Right alignment :( ctl+R) we can make Right alignment to the selected text.\r\n \r\n\r\niii)Centre alignment :( ctl+E) we can make centre alignment to the selected text.\r\n \r\niv)Justify: (ctrl+J) we can make Justify alignment to the selected text.\r\n \r\nv)Line spacing: We change the spacing between the lines of text.eg:1.0,1.15,1.5etc \r\n \r\nvi)Shading: Color the background behind the text or paragraph.\r\n \r\nvii)Bottom boarder: customize the borders of the selected text or cell.\r\n \r\nviii)Bullets: Start the bulleted list; click the arrow to different bulleted styles.\r\n \r\nix)Numbering: Start the numbered list, click the arrow  to choose different numbering formats\r\n \r\nx)Multilevel list: Start multilevel list, click the arrow to choose different multilevel styles\r\n \r\nxi)Decrease indent: Decreases the indent level of paragraph\r\nxii)Increase indent: Increases the indent level of paragraph\r\nxiii)Sort: Alphabetize the selected data or sort the numerical data\r\nxiv)Show/hide: show paragraph marks and other hidden formatting symbols\r\n4)Styles\r\ni)Normal: Format titles, quotes, and other text using this gallery of styles. \r\nii)No spacing: Format titles, quotes, and other text using this gallery of styles.\r\niii)Heading 1: Format titles, quotes, and other text using this gallery of styles.\r\niv)Heading 2: Format titles, quotes, and other text using this gallery of styles.\r\nv)Change styles: Format titles, quotes, and other text using this gallery of styles.\r\n5)Editing\r\ni)Find: (ctl+F) Find the text  in the document\r\n\r\nii)Replace: (ctl+H) Replace the text  in the document\r\n \r\niii)Select: Select text or objects in the document \r\n &#8195;\r\n','130','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (72,1,'a','a)input device-helps to give input to the computer eg keyboard mouse joystick etc b)output device-gives computer processed information eg monitor printer projector c)CPU 1)control unit-controls the different units of a computer 2)ALU -it does the airthmatic and logic operations \r\nall the units are inter connected by buses\r\nmemory-primary and secondary memory-used to store the data and process the information','132','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
