 (73,1,'b','home menu of MS DOC \r\nhome menu consists of fallowing sub menus \r\n1.clipboard \r\n2.font\r\n3.paragraph \r\n4.styles \r\n5.editing\r\n\r\nclipboard - in clipboardwe have fallowing options \r\n1.cut-used to cut any file image or any contents of the document\r\n2.copy - used to copy any file image or contents of the document \r\n3.paste- those things which has been cut or copied earlier can be pasted any where in the document.\r\n\r\nFont- in the font option we have fallowing options.\r\nfont- to select the font face.\r\ngrow font and shrink font -to increase or decrease the font size.\r\nclear formatting-to undo any changes done to the text of the documents.\r\nbold- to make text in bold letters.\r\nitalic-for cursive writing.\r\nunderline-to underline the text. \r\nstrike through- to draw a line in between the texts.\r\ntext case- to alter between any form of cases.\r\n font colour- to change the font colour.\r\n\r\n\r\nparagraph \r\na-Bullets: To assign bullets to the lines\r\nb-numbering -to assign the numbers to the line\r\nc-aligning options-four options to align text to right, left ,centre and justify(adjusting the space between texts to meet the right and left indices of the page )\r\nstyles-to choose the text styles.\r\n\r\nediting\r\nfind option to find any letter or word in the document\r\nreplace - to replace a word with other word.\r\nselect- to select a text or object in the document.\r\n','135','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (74,1,'b','Home menu options consists of the following options, they are\r\n1.CLIPBOARD- It consists of various sub options.\r\n(a)CUT-It will cut the contents and put it on the clipboard.\r\n(b)COPY-It will copy the text in the documents.\r\n(C)PASTE-Paste the contents of the clipboard.\r\n2.FONT:It consists of various sub options.\r\n     I. Style:\r\n    ii. size: size of the font will be changed \r\n    iv. Underline: underline the selected text.\r\n    v. Italic: Ialicize the selected text.\r\n3.Paragraph\r\n        I. Align left: Align text to the left.\r\n       ii. Align right: :Align text to the right.\r\n      iii. Center: center text.\r\n\r\n\r\n','143','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
