 (79,1,'c','PRINT PREVIEW:\r\n1)Print: To print the document.\r\n2)Options: To change the printing options.\r\n3)Margins: To get or to change the margin size of the document.\r\n4)Orientations: To change the page orientation between portrait or landscape.\r\n5)Preview: To check the document how it looks before final print.\r\n6)Zoom: To increase or decrease the size off the selected text.\r\n7)Magnifiers: To change the zooming of the selected content.\r\n8)Show rulers: To measure rulers and line up condition. \r\n9)Close : To close the current document. \r\n','127','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (80,1,'BB','HOME MENU:1)CLIPBOARD\r\n          1)CUT 2)COPY 3)PASTE\r\n          2)FONT\r\n          1)BOLD 2) ITALIC 3)UNDERLINE\r\n          4)STRIKE THROUGH 5)TEXT THROUGH\r\n          TEXT SHADOW 7)CHARCTER SPACING\r\n         3) PARAGRAPH\r\n         1)BULLET 2)NUMBERING 3)MULTILEVEL LIST 4)DECREASE INDENT\r\n         5)INCREASE INDENT 6)SORT SHOW HIDE7) CHANGE CASE\r\n         8)INCREASE FONT SIZE 9)CLEAR ALL FORMATING ','140','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (81,1,'c','print preview-used to go through the document once before printing it . \r\nhas following options\r\nprint-to print the document.\r\noptions-to alter the printing properties\r\n\r\npage setup\r\nmargins-to arrange the margin.\r\norientation-change to portrait or in landscape format.\r\nsize-to adjust the size of paper. \r\n\r\npreview\r\nzoom in- enlarge and view whole document\r\nzoom out- shrink the document\r\n\r\npreview\r\nnext page - goes to next page\r\nprevious page-goes to previous page.\r\nclose preview-closes the print preview option.','135','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
