 (82,1,'b','Home contains the followings:\r\n1.clipboard:\r\n   a.cut(ctrl+x)\r\n   b.copy(ctrl+c)\r\n   c.paste(ctrl+v)\r\n2.fonts:\r\n   a.bold(ctrl+b)\r\n   b.italic(ctrl+i)\r\n   c.underline(ctrl+u)\r\n   d.strike through\r\n   e.subscript(ctrl+=)\r\n   f.superscript(ctrl+shift++)\r\n   g.change case\r\n   h.font color\r\n   i.grow font(ctrl+>) \r\n   j.shrink font(ctrl+<)\r\n   \r\n   \r\n3.paragraph:\r\n   a.bullets\r\n   b.numbering\r\n   c.multilevel list\r\n   d.sort\r\n   e.decrease indent\r\n   f.increase indent\r\n   g.align text right(ctrl+r)\r\n   h.center\r\n   i.justify\r\n   j.line spacing\r\n   k.shading\r\n   l.bottom border\r\n   m.align text left(ctrl+l)\r\n4.styles:\r\n   a.normal\r\n   b.heading\r\n   c.change styles\r\n5.editing:\r\n   a.find\r\n   b.replace\r\n   c.select','158','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (83,1,'c','option print preview of ms word\r\n *PRINT PREVIEW-To preview and makes changes to document in before printing.\r\nthis option is consists of following  sub options.\r\na)print\r\nb)options:use to change how document appears in display.\r\nc)page setup: it consist of margins, orientation,and size of the pages\r\nd)zoom:his option is used to zoom and page width\r\ne)preview option: this have the options called magnifier and show ruler options to preview the document. ','137','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (84,1,'b','HOME\r\n1.CLIP BORD\r\n    a. cut-To cut the document\r\n    b. copy-To copy the given data or document.\r\n    c. Paste-To paste the data or document.\r\n2. FONT\r\n    a. Bold- bold the letter\r\n    b. Italic- Italic the given document or data.\r\n    c. under line-under line the selected data or document.\r\n    d. strike through- To strike through the selected data.\r\n    e. super script- the given below the data highlight.\r\n    f. sub script- the given above the data highlight.\r\n    g. font size-  To select the font size.\r\n    h. font colour- TO select the document colour.\r\n    i. font style- to select the font style.\r\n3. PARAGRAPH\r\n    a. bullets-start a bulleted list.\r\n    b. numbering-start a numbered list.\r\n    c. multilevel list- start a multi level list.\r\n    d. decrease indent-to decrease the given data.\r\n    e. increase indent- to increase the given data.\r\n    f. sort- alphabetize the selected text or sort numerical data.\r\n    g. centre text- text align to the centre. \r\n    h. align text left- text align to the left.\r\n    i. align text right- align text to the right.\r\n    j. justify- align text both left and right margins.\r\n    k. line spacing- change the spacing between lines of text.\r\n    l. shading- colour the back ground behind the selected text or paragraph.\r\n    m.  bottom border-customize the borders of the selected cells or text.  ','129','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (85,1,'b','1.HOME MENU\r\na.Cut:(ctrl+x)>It will move the specific selected document\r\nb.Copy : (ctrl+c)> It will copy the specific selected document     c.Paste :(ctrl+v)> It will paste the specific selected document    2. FONT\r\na. Style: It will change letter style the specific selected document\r\nb. Size: (ctrl+[) It will change letter size the specific selected\r\nc.GROW FONT : Increase font size\r\nd.SHRINK FONT :Decrease font size \r\ne.CLEAR FORMATTING :Clear all the formatting from the selection\r\nf.Bold : (ctrl+B) Make the selected text bold\r\ng.Underline (Ctrl+U)To underline selected word\r\nh.Italic:(ctrl+I)To change letter to italic\r\ni.STRIKETHRUGH:Draw a line through the middle of the select text\r\nj.CHANGE CASE\r\n 1.Lower Case:To make all letters are small Letters\r\n 2.Upper Case: To make all letters are capital Letters\r\n 3.Sentence Case: To make all words are sentence word\r\n 4.Toggle Case: To make in word first letter is small letter other   letters are capital\r\nk.SUPERSCRIPT:(ctrl+shift++)Create the small letters blow the text line\r\nl.SUBSCRIPT: create small letter below the text baseline\r\n3.PARAGRAPH\r\n1.Bullets: To choose different bullets style\r\n2.Numbering: To choose different numbering formats\r\n3.Multilevel list: To choose different Multilevel list style\r\n4.Decrease indent: Decreases the indent level of the paragraph\r\n5.Increase indent: Increase the indent level of the paragraph\r\n6.Sort:  Alphbetize the selected text or sort numerical data\r\n7.Show/hide: Show paragraph marks and other hidden formatting symbols\r\n8.Align\r\n a.left : (ctrl+L) Align text to the left\r\n b. centre :(ctrl+C) Align text to the centre\r\n C .Right :(ctrl+R) Align text to the right\r\n d. Justify (ctrl+J): Align text to both the left and right margins, adding extra space between words necessary\r\n9.Line spacing: Change the spacing between lines of text\r\n10.Shading: Colour the background behind the selected text or paragraph\r\n11.Bottom border: Customize the border of the selected cells or text                         \r\n  ','139','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (86,1,'c','Print preview means make changes to page before print.a)it use to resige the width of the print page.b)make page to zoom.c)use to changes to the paper size.c)it resize the page margins.d)to change the printing options.e)use to take content to the one or two pages.','150','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (87,1,'b','Home menu options: a.Clipboard:- 1.Cut->(Ctrl+X)->It is used to cut and to put the selected document on clipboard. 2.Copy->(Ctrl+C)-> It is Used to copy and to put it on clipboard. 3.Paste->(Ctrl+V)-> It is used to paste the selected document. b.Font:- 1.Style:It is used to style the content. 2.Size:It is used to increase or decrease the size of the selected document. 3.Bold:used to make the bold style of the document. 4.Italic:used to make the italic style of the document. 5.Underline:Used to underline the document. 6.strikethrough:Used to strike the document. 7.Superscript and Subscript:Used to create small letters. 8.Change case:Used to change the case of document. c.Paragraph: 1.Bullet: 2.Numbering: 3.Multilevel list: 4.Decrease indent 5.Increase indent 6.sort 7.show/hide 8.Alignment d.Styles: (Alt+Ctrl+Shift+S) - used to Show the styles window. e.editing: 1. Find: (Ctrl+F) -> Used to Find text in the document. 2.Replace: (Ctrl+H) -> used to Replace text in the document. 3.Select: ->Select text or objects in the document.','160','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (88,1,'b','Home menu consists of following sub menus\r\nClipBoard\r\nFont\r\nParagraph\r\nStyles\r\nEditing\r\na)Clipboard\r\n1)Cut-used to cut a portion of selected text.(Ctrl+x)\r\n2)Copy-used to copy a portion of selected text.(Ctrl+c)\r\n3)Paste-used to paste a text in the document.(Ctrl+v)\r\n4)Clear formatting-use to all applied effects\r\n\r\nb)Font\r\n1)Font-used to apply a font style to the text.\r\n2)Font colour-to apply a font colour to the text.\r\n3)Font size-to apply suitable font size to the text.\r\n4)Bold-used to create bold text(ctrl+b)\r\n5)Italics-used to create a italicized text.(ctrl+i)\r\n6)Underline-used to under line the selected text.(ctrl+u)\r\n7)Grow/shrink font-used to grow(ctrl+])or shrink(ctrl+[) the size of the text.\r\n8)Strikethrough-to apply strikethrough formatting style to the text\r\n9)Change case-to convert the text to uppercase or lower case.\r\n10)Superscript-to insert letter or number above the text\r\n11)Subscript-to insert letter or number below the text.\r\n12)Highlight text-to highlight a particular text in the document.\r\n\r\nc)Paragraph\r\n1)Bullets and Numbering-to apply a bullets or numbering pattern into the paragraph.\r\n2)Increase or Decrease Indent-to increase or the decrease indentation between the lines in a paragraph.\r\n3)Line spacing-to provide spacing between lines in a paragraph.\r\n4)Sort-to sort the given text in  numerical or alphabetical order.\r\n5)Multilevel list-used to apply multi level numbering to the text.\r\n6)Show/Hide-Used  to show or hide contents of the document like formatting options, symbols and equations\r\n7)Background-to apply background to the paragraph.\r\n8)Align text-used to align the text left(ctrl+l),right(ctrl+r),centre(ctrl+f) and justify the text(ctrl+j)\r\n\r\nd)Styles-Used to apply different styles to a text in the document \r\n\r\ne)Editing\r\n1)find-to find a particular text in the document.(Ctrl+f)\r\n2)replace-to replace a particular text in the document.(Ctrl+h)\r\n3)select-to select a text in the document.(ctrl+a)used to select entire text.\r\n\r\n','149','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (89,1,'a','block diagram of computer:\r\ninput:we will give the command to computer through input devices like keaboard,scanner,joystick,etc..\r\nthis will take in the binary form(0,1) \r\ncentral processing unit :\r\nit will contain 3 parts \r\ncontrol unit:the message from input devices received by control unit passes to Arithmetic and logical unit.\r\nALU: the message from control unit received by ALU will be tranfered to memory unit \r\nmemory unit:it transfers the input to output devices\r\noutput : it will display the answer what we want through output devices like monitor,printer etc...','146','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (90,1,'b','In home option mainly consists of clipboard, Font, paragraph, styles. Clip board- It consists of cut, copy, paste. cut option selected text to cut. Copy(ctrl+c) selected text to copy. Paste(ctrl+v)- selected text to paste it.\r\nFONT- 1)Font(ctrl+shift+F)- changes the font face.\r\n2) Font size(ctrl+shift+P)-changes the font face.\r\n3)GRow font- increases the font size\r\n4) shrink font- Decrease the font size.\r\n5)Bold(ctrl+B)- make the selected text bold.\r\n6)Italic(ctrl+I)- make the selected italin.\r\n7)Underline(ctrl+U)- make the selected text underline.\r\n8)subscript- The text below text in small size.\r\n9)super script- The text above the text small size.\r\n\r\nParagraph- \r\n1)Bullets-\r\n2)Numbering-\r\n3)Decrease Indent- Page will decrease indent. \r\n4)Increase Indent- Page will increase indent.\r\n5)Align text left- Align text in left of the margin.\r\n6)Align text right- Align the text in right if the margin.\r\n7)center- Align text in center\r\n8)Justify-The text in canter full margin.\r\n Styles- The text can type in different styles and format.\r\nEdit- the select text edited.\r\nsearch - Typed text to be searched.\r\n\r\n\r\n','161','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (91,1,'a','COMPUTER IS COMBONATION OF SOFTWARE AND HARDWARE,COMPUTER CONSISTS OF\r\nINPUT DEVICES AND OUTPUT DEVICES.\r\ninput devices:-keyboard, mouse, pan drive, note pad,compact disk, \r\nscanner,\r\noutput devices:-monitor, printer.\r\nMOTHERBOARD:-\r\n1)ALIGIBRA \r\n2)CPU\r\n3)DEVICES\r\n*HEART OF THE COMPUTER IS CENTRAL PROCESSING UNIT\r\nCPU is the main port of computer and it contains fully work from this part \r\n*ALIGIBRA is the functions are any calculations in the computer, and its help for output and input devices also ','138','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (92,1,'b','Home Menu consists of the following\r\n1.Clipboard\r\n2.Fonts\r\n3.Paragraph\r\n4.Editing\r\nClipboard:\r\na)Cut(ctrl+X): used to cut the selected text of the document.\r\nb)Copy(ctrl+C): used to copy the selected text of the document.\r\nc)Paste(ctrl+V): used to paste the selected text of the document.\r\nFonts:\r\na)style: used to apply various styles to the selected text of the document.\r\nb)Size: used to change the size of the selected text of the document.\r\nc)Bold(ctrl+B):used to make the selected text Bold.\r\nd)Italic(ctrl+I): used to italicize the selected text.\r\ne)Underline(ctrl+U): used to underline the selected text.\r\nf)Strikethrough: used to strike the selected text.\r\ng)Subscript: used to apply numbers below the text.\r\nh)Superscript: used to apply numbers above the text.\r\ni)change case: used to change upper case to lowercase of the selected text\r\nj)Highlight: used to highlight the selected text.\r\nk)colour font: used to change the font colour of the selected text.\r\nParagraph\r\na)Bullets: used to start a bulleted list.\r\nb)Numbering: used to start a numbered list.\r\nc)Multilevel list: Used to start a Multilevel list.\r\nd)Line spacing: used to increase, decrease or remove space in between lines.\r\ne)Left alignment(ctrl+L): used to align the selected text to left.\r\nf)Right alignment(ctrl+R): used to align the selected text to right.\r\ng)Centre alignment(ctrl+E): used to align the selected text to the centre.\r\nh) Justify(ctrl+J): used to justify the selected text of the document.\r\ni) Increase Indent: used to increase the size of the selected text.\r\nj) Decrease Indent: used to decrease the size of the selected text.\r\nk)sort text: sort text in numerical order.\r\nl)Shading: shade text in the document.\r\nm)show/hide: used to show or hide the selected document.\r\nEditing\r\na) find(ctrl+F): to find the selected word in the document\r\nb) replace : to replace the selected word in the document.\r\nc) select: to select the text in the document.','148','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (93,1,'c','PRINT PREVIEW : Preview and make changes to pages before printing. PRINT PREVIEW OPTIONS are-\r\n1.PRINT\r\n2.PAGE SETUP: It has the following sub options,\r\n(a)MARGINS: Select the margin.\r\n(b)orientation: switch the page orientation between the portrait and landscape.\r\n3.ZOOM\r\n4.PREVIEW. ','143','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (94,1,'b','HOME:1)Clipboard 2)Font 3)Paragraph 4)Styles 5)editing\r\n\r\n1)Clipboard:a)Cut(ctrl+X):Cut the selection from the\r\n document and put it on the clipboard\r\nb)Copy(ctrl+C):Copy the selection and put it on the clipboard\r\nc)Paste(ctrl+V):paste the document which is copied or cutted\r\nd)Format Painter(ctrl+shift+C):Copy formatting from one place and put it on the other place\r\n2)Font:a)Font(ctrl+shift+F):Change the font face\r\nb)Font Size(ctrl+shift+P):Change the font size\r\nc)Grow Font(Ctrl+>):Increase the font size\r\nd)Shrink Font(ctrl+<):Decrease the font size\r\ne)Clear Formating:Clear format from the selection\r\nf)Bold(ctrl+B):Make the selected text bold\r\ng)Italic(ctrl+I):Italicise the selected text\r\nh)Underline(ctrl+U):Underline the selected text\r\ni)Strikethrough:Draw a line to the middle of the selected text\r\nj)Subscript(ctrl+=):Create a small letter below the text base line\r\nk)Superscript(ctrl+shift++):Crete a small letter above the line of text\r\nl)ChangeCase:Change all the selected text to UPPERCASE,lowercase\r\nm)Text Highlight Color:Make text look like it was marked like a highlightor pen\r\nn)Font Color:Change the text color\r\n3)Paragraph:a)Bullet:start a bulleted list\r\nb)Numbering:Start a numbering list\r\nc)Multilevel list:Start a multilevel list\r\nd)Decrease indent:Decrease the indent level of the paragraph\r\ne)Increase indent:Increase the indent level of the paragraph\r\nf)Sort:Alphabetise selected data or sort numbering\r\ng)Align Text Left(ctrl+L):align text to the left\r\nh)Center Align(ctrl+E):Align center\r\ni)Align Text Right(ctrl+R):Align text to the right\r\nj)Justify(ctrl+j):Align text to both left and right margins\r\nk)Line Spacing:Change line between spacing\r\n5)Editing:a)Find(ctrl+F):Find text in the document\r\nb)Replace(ctrl+H):Replace text in the document\r\nc)select:select text or objects in the document','128','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (96,1,'A','CONSIST OF THREE POINS 1 INPUT 2 CPU 3 OUTPUT\r\nPRINT 1) INPUT IT MEANS WALKEABEL DATA WE GIVIN TO THE INPUT\r\nINPUT PARTS LIKE KEYBOARD MOUSE \r\n2)CPU) CENTER PROSSESING UNIT IT FORFORMS ARTHEMATIC LOGIC UNIT IT IS BRAIN OF THE COMPUTER\r\n3)OUTPUT : IT MEANS COMPUTER SHOWS MONITOR ','140','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
