 (98,1,'c','print preview contains the followings:\r\n\r\n      1.print:\r\n        a)print\r\n        b)options \r\n      2.page setup:\r\n        a)mrgin\r\n        b)orientation\r\n        c)size\r\n      3.zoom:\r\n        a)one page\r\n        b)two page\r\n        c)page width\r\n      4.preview:\r\n        a)next page\r\n        b)previous page\r\n        c) shrink one page  \r\n','157','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (99,1,'C','Print:( ctrl+P): To print documents\r\na.Print: select a printer number of copies\r\nb.Quick print: send the document directly to default printer without making changes\r\nc.Preview print: preview & make changes to page before printing\r\n  1.Options: open the options dialog box in which you can change printing\r\nPage setup: show the page setup dialog box\r\n    Margins: select the margins size for the entire documents or current selection\r\nOrientation: switch the pages portrait & landscape layouts\r\nSize: choose a paper size for the current section\r\nZoom: open the zoom dialog box to specify the zoom lelel of the document \r\nOne page: zoom the document so that an entire page fits in the window \r\nTwo page: zoom the document so that an two pages fits the window\r\nPage width: zoom the document so that the width of the page Matches the width of the window\r\n   Preview:\r\na.Show view: view the rulers used to measure &line up object in the document\r\nb.Magnifier: Turn the mouse cursor into a magnifying glass which can be used yo quickly toggle between 100%& fit whole page zoom level through clacking the document\r\nc.Shrink to fit: Attempt to shrink document by one page by slightly reducing the size & spacing of the text\r\nd.Next page: Navigate to the next page of the document\r\ne.Previous page: Navigate to the previous page of the document\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n                                                                                                ','139','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (100,1,'b','1. Clipboard a. Cut : cut the selection from the Document. b. Copy : copy the selection. c. Paste: pastes the contents of clipboard. 2. Font a. Font style: Change the font face. b. Font size: Change the font size. c. Bold: Make the selected text bold. d. Italic: Italicize the selected text. e. Underline: Underline the selected text. f. Strikethrough: Draw a line through middle of the Selected text. g. Subscript: Create small letter below the text Baseline . h. Superscript: Create small letter above the text. i. Change case: change all the text to upper case, Lower case etc. j. Grow font: increase the font size. k. Shrink font: decrease the font size. l. Texts highlight colour: Text background. m. Font colour: Change the text colour. n. Clear formatting: Clear all the formatting from the selection text, leaving only the plain text. 3. Paragraph a. Bullet: Starts a bullet list. b. Numbering: Starts a numbering list. c. Multilevel list: Starts a multilevel list. d. Align Text left e. Align Text right f. Centre g. Justify h. Decrease indent: Decreases indent level of the Paragraph. i. Increase indent: Increases indent level of the Paragraph. j. Line spacing: Change the spacing between lines Of the text. k. Shading: background colour to the text. l. Sort: alphabetize the selected text. m. Show/hide n. Bottom border: 4. Style 5. Editing a. Find b. Replace','153','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
