 (102,1,'c','print preview\r\n1.print:\r\na)print\r\nb)options\r\n\r\n2.page setup:\r\na)margins\r\nb)orientation\r\nc)size\r\n\r\n3.zoom:\r\na)zoom\r\nb)100%\r\nc)one page \r\nd)two page\r\ne)page width\r\n\r\n4.preview:\r\na)show ruler\r\nb)magnifier\r\nc)shrink one page\r\nd)next page\r\ne)previous page\r\n\r\n5.close print preview:\r\n','158','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (103,1,'b','Home menu options :-1)Clipboard 2)Font 3)Paragraph 4)Styles 5)Editing 1)Clipboard consists paste, copy, cut and format painter 2)Font used to increase ,decrease , bold ,underline font. 5)Editing options are :-Find ,Replace and Select words in the documents. ','156','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (104,1,'b',' Home:\r\n1.Clipboard \r\na.Cut(ctrl+x)\r\n \r\nCut the selection from the document and put it on the clipboard.\r\n  b.Copy(ctrl+c)\r\nCopy the selection and put it on the clipboard. \r\n  a.Paste(ctrl+v)\r\nPaste the contents of the clipboard.\r\n  e.Font \r\nf.Bold(ctrl+b)\r\nMake the selected text bold.\r\n   a.Italic(ctrl+i)\r\nItalicize the selected text. \r\nb.Underline(ctrl+u)\r\nUnderline the selected text.\r\n  a.Subscript(ctrl+=)\r\nCreate small letters bellow the text baseline.\r\nb.Superscript(ctrl+shift++)\r\nCreate small letters above the line of text.\r\n   a.Text highlight colour\r\nMake text look like it was marked with highlighter pen.\r\nb.Font colour\r\nChange the text colour.\r\n   2.Paragraph \r\na.Bullets\r\nStart a bullet list.\r\nClick the arrow to choose different bullet styles.\r\n  a.Multilevel list\r\nStart a multilevel list.\r\nClick the arrow to choose different multilevel list styles.\r\nb.Numbering\r\nStart a numbering list.\r\n  a.Sort\r\nAlphabetize the selected text or sort numerical data.\r\n  g.Align text left\r\nAlign text on the left.\r\n  a.Center\r\nCenter text.\r\nb.Align text right\r\nAlign text on the right.\r\n  a.Justify\r\nAlign text on both the left and right margins, adding extra space between words as necessary\r\n  k.Line spacing\r\nChange the spacing between the lines of text.\r\n  3.Styles \r\na.Change styles\r\nChange the set of styles, colours and fonts used in the document.   \r\n\r\n ','147','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (105,1,'c','when we gave the instruction to the computer it work that and we want the output of that work as hardcopy then we use printer before that once we check the what we selected data is correct or not then we use option called print preview and  it contain the below options.\r\nPrint-\r\na)print- it will give hard copy of that we selected.\r\nb)obtions\r\nPAGE SETUP-\r\na)margins\r\nb)oriantations- this have two options 1)landscape 2)portrait\r\nc)size-it has different types of paper sizes ex-letter,A4 size,small letter size etc.\r\n3)ZOOM-it has choice to see the what we select the data ant any mistakes in the selected text.\r\n\r\n','145','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (106,1,'b','HOME MENU\r\nCLIPBOARD\r\nCUT(CTRL+X): Cut the selection from the document\r\nCOPY(CTRL+C): Copy selection from document\r\nPASTE(CTRL+V): Paste the contents of the clipboard\r\n\r\nFONT\r\nBOLD:(CTRL+B): MAKE THE SELECTED TEXT BOARD\r\nITALIC(CTRL+I): Italicize selected text\r\nUNDERLINE(CTRL+U): UNDERLINE SELECTED TEXT\r\nFONT COLOR: Change the text color\r\nGROW FONT(CTRL+>): Increase font size\r\nSHRINK FONT(CTRL+<): Decrease font size\r\n \r\nSTYLE\r\nCHANGE STYLE: Change the set of style fonts used in this document\r\n\r\nEDITTING\r\nFIND(CTRL+F): Find text in the document\r\nREPLACE(CTRL+H): Replace text in the document\r\nSELECT : Select text or object in document','151','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (107,1,'c','PRINT PREVIEW OPTIONS :-1)Print 2)Page setup 3)Zoom 4)Preview 1)Print option consists of print ant options. Print prints the document and Option gives the printing option. 2) Page setup-we can setup Margins ,Orientations and Size. 3)Zoom - It is used to enlarge and shrink the page. 4)Preview - It is used to see the document before print. ','156','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (108,1,'a','computer mainly contains following devices\r\nCPU,Input devices,Out PUt devices\r\n CPU-CPU is the heart of the computer it contains memory unit, processer, busses. MEMORY->used to read and write the data in to IO devices and processor. There are 2 types of memory. 1)Main memory-Its the temporary memory called as volatile memory, its directly communicate with processor. 2)Secondary memory- Its the permanent memory used to store the data. eg:-Hard disk, CD, DVD, USB drive etc Processing unit:- Its receives the instructions and data from Input devices then process the data and give the result in to output device. it mainly contains ALU and Control unit.\r\nArithmatic unit perform the arithmatic operations.\r\neg:-1+2,1*2\r\nLogical unit perform the logical operations.\r\nEg:- A And B, A OR B\r\n\r\nInput devices recieves data from user and write in to memory.\r\nEG:-keyboard, mouse,joy stick,scanner.\r\nOutput device read the dat from memory and give it to user.\r\nEg:-Monitor,printer,projector etc.','155','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (109,1,'c','PRINT PREVIEW OPTIONS:-\r\nPRINT\r\n1)PRINT \r\n2)OPTIONS\r\nPAGE SETUP\r\n1)MARGINS\r\n2)ORIENTATION\r\n3)SIZE\r\nZOOM\r\n1)ONE PAGE\r\n2)TWO PAGE\r\n3)PAGE WIDTH\r\nPREVIEWS\r\n1)SHOW RULER\r\n2)MAGNIFIER\r\n3)NEXT PAGE\r\n4)PREVIOUS\r\nCLOSE PRINT PREVEIW\r\n\r\n','138','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (110,1,'c','The various options in print Preview menu are\r\n1)Print\r\na)print-to print the document.(ctrl+p)\r\nb)options-provides dialog box to change printing options.\r\n\r\n\r\n2)Page Setup\r\na)Size-used to provide the size of current page.\r\nb)Orientation-used to switch between portrait and landscape.\r\nc)Margin-provides margin size for selected text or entire document\r\n\r\n\r\n3)Zoom\r\na)Zoom-used to specify the zoom level of the document.\r\nb)100%-to zoom the document to 100% of the original size.\r\nc)One page-zoom the document so that entire page fits the window.\r\nd)Two Page-zooms the document so that two pages fit the window.\r\ne)page width-zooms such that width of the page matches the width of the window.\r\n\r\n\r\n4)Preview\r\na)Show ruler:-helps to view the ruler used in alignment.\r\nb)Magnifier:-helps to toggle between 100% and fit whole page zoom automatically.\r\nc)Shrink one page:-attempts to shrink the document by one page reducing the size and spacing between words.\r\nd)Next page: - navigate to next page of the document.\r\ne)Previous page:-navigate to previous page of the document.\r\nf)Close print preview:-close the print preview and return to the editing document.\r\n','149','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (111,1,'b','HOME menu consists CLIPBOARD : has following options \r\ncut : to cut the selected text\r\ncopy: copy the selected text\r\npaste : paste the content of clipboard\r\nformat painter : copy formatting from one place add it to another place.\r\n2 FONT \r\na)Italic : italicize the text\r\nb) Font : change the font face\r\nc)font size: change the font size\r\n\r\nd)Bold : make the selected text bold\r\ne)Underline :  underline selected text                \r\nf)text highlighter : make text look like it was marked with highlighter pen\r\ng)Font colour : change the text colour\r\n3 PARAGRAPH \r\na)bullets: make bullet the list\r\nb)numbering : make numbering the list \r\nc)multilevel list: make multilevel list \r\nd)align text right : align text to right \r\ne)align text left : align text to left\r\nf)centre: centre the text\r\ng)shading: colour the background of text or paragraph\r\n4 STYLES\r\n5 EDITING are the options in HOME menu \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','159','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
INSERT INTO `tblanswer` (`answerid`,`main`,`submain`,`answer`,`username`,`testdate`,`coorectionstatus`,`score`,`subjectname`) VALUES 
 (112,1,'b','Home menu\r\nCut (ctrl+x):  It is used to cut the data.\r\nCopy (ctrl+c): It used to copy the data.\r\nPast (ctrl+v): It use to past the data.\r\n\r\nFont:\r\nFont style (ctrl+shift+F): I t used to change the font face\r\nFont size (ctrl+shift+p): It used to change the font size\r\nFont colour: It used to change the text colour.\r\nBold (ctrl+b): Make the selected text bold.\r\nItalic (ctrl+i): Make the selected text italic. \r\nUnderline (ctrl+u): underline the selected text\r\n\r\nSuperscript (ctrl+shift++): create the small letters above the line of text.\r\nSubscript (ctrl+=): Create the small letters below the text baseline.\r\nChange case:\r\nSentence case\r\nLowercase\r\nUppercase\r\nCapitalize each word\r\ntoGGLE   cASE\r\n\r\nParagraph:\r\nRight alignment (ctrl+r): Align text to the right. \r\n \r\nLeft alignment (ctrl+b): Align text to the left.\r\nCentre alignment (ctrl+c): Align text to the centre.  \r\nJustify (ctrl+j): Align text to both the left and right margins.\r\nLine spacing (ctrl+b): Change the spacing between lines of text\r\nDecrease indent: Decrease the indent level of the paragraph.\r\nIncrease indent: Increase the indent level of the paragraph.\r\nSort: Alphabetize the selected text or sort numerical data.\r\nShading: color the background behind the selected text or paragraph.\r\nBorder: Draw the table / border to the text or paragraph.\r\n\r\nStyles: change the set of styles, colors and fonts used in this document. \r\n\r\nEditing:\r\nFind (ctrl+F): Find text in the document.\r\nReplace (ctrl+H): Replace the text in the document.\r\nSelect: Select text or objects in the document.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','141','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (114,1,'a','computer is an electronic device which makes multiple actions. The block diagram of computer consists of INPUT->CPU->OUTPUT 1.INPUT-is a device through which we can give information to perform particular actions. EX: keyboard, mouse 2 CPU: is a central processing unit which is brain of computer. It takes information and converts into its machine language and gives output. CPU consists of CONTROL UNIT: which controls the commands of the computer. ALU : arithmetic and logical unit which performs all mathematical calculations. 3 OUTPUT: is an information we get it through output devices such as monitor, scanner.\r\n\r\n','159','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
