 (116,1,'c','Print preview: A.Print\r\n1)Print\r\n2)options\r\nB.Page setup\r\n1)Margins\r\n2)Orientation\r\n3)Size\r\nc.Zoom\r\n1)Zoom\r\n2)One page\r\n3)Two page\r\n4)Page width\r\nD.Preview\r\n1)Show ruler\r\n2)Magnifier\r\n3)Shrink one page\r\n4)Next page\r\n5)Previous page\r\n6)Close print preview','130','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (117,1,'c','  Print preview \r\nPrint\r\n\r\nOptions\r\n   Open the option dialog box, in which you can change printing options.\r\n  Page setup\r\nMargins\r\n   Select the margin sizes for the entire document or the current section.\r\n  Preview\r\nShow ruler \r\n View the rulers, used to measure and line up objects in the document.\r\n\r\nMagnifier\r\n   Turn the mouse curser into a magnifying glass which can be used to quickly toggle between100% and fit whole page zoom levels through clicking the document.\r\n Shrink one page\r\n    Attempt to shrink the document by one page by slightly reducing the size and spacing of the text.\r\n\r\nNext page \r\n   Navigate to the next page of the document.\r\nPrevious page\r\n   Navigate to the previous page of the document.\r\n  Close print preview \r\n   Close the print preview and return to editing the document.\r\n  PRINT:\r\nName:\r\n Select the printer name which is connected to the system through which you wanted to print the document.  \r\nStatus: \r\nIdle\r\nType:\r\nWhere:\r\nComment:\r\n  Page range:\r\nAll: \r\nAll pages of your document will be printed.\r\nCurrent page: \r\nOnly current page will be printed.\r\nPages:\r\nSelect the page numbers, only between this page numbers will be printed.\r\nCopies:\r\n Select how much copies of your document you want.\r\nNumber of copies:\r\nCollate:\r\nTo print back to back pages.\r\nScale the paper size:\r\n','147','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (118,1,'c','Print Preview options:\r\n1)Show Ruler: use the rules, used to measure line up objects in the document,.\r\n2)Magnifier: used to magnify the selected page of the document.\r\n3)Shrink: attempt to shrink document by one page by slightly reducing the size spacing of the text.\r\n4)Next page:used to navigate to the next page of the document. \r\n5)Previous page: used to navigate to the previous page of the document.\r\n6)close Print preview: used to close the selected page.','148','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
