 (119,1,'c','The print preview option consists of Print, page set up, Zoom, Preview ,close print Preview.\r\nprint(ctrl+P)-Print the selected page.\r\nPage set up-1)margin- The page margin left, right.\r\n2) Orientation- In orientation there are two types portrait, landscape. \r\n3)page size- select  page size\r\n\r\n ZOOM\r\n1) zoom- It zoom the page \r\n2) 100/ - 100/ zoom option it zooms only 100/\r\n\r\npreview- when you click preview option it show the page which page to be print and ask to print which orientation ,etc\r\nIn print preview option close print preview showing . close print preview is close the print preview if any error in page. if no error in page directly print.\r\n','161','27/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
