 (314,8,'6','   The options found in animation menu are\r\n   1)Preview-used to preview the effects or transitions applied to the slide.\r\n\r\n   2)Animations\r\n    a)Animate:-Used to apply animations to objects in the slide.\r\n    b)Custom Animations:-Used to animate individual objects of the slide.\r\n\r\n   3)Transitions to the slide\r\n    a)Transition Sound:-Used to apply transition sound between slides.\r\n    b)Transition Speed:-To choose how fast to animate the transition between slides.\r\n    c)Apply To All:-To apply the current transition to all slides.\r\n    d)On Mouse Click:-Wait until mouse click to move to next slide.\r\n    e)Automatically After:-Move to next slide after a few seconds.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','149','29/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (315,1,'2','animations\r\n','138','29/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (316,8,'6','  \r\nAnimations\r\n1)Animate: Choose an animation to apply to objects in the slide.\r\nNo Animation: Choose an animation to apply to objects in the slide.\r\nCustom animation: Open the custom animation task. you can animate individual objects on the slide.\r\nTransition to this slide\r\nTransition Sound: Select a sound to play during the transition between the previous slide and the current slide.\r\n\r\nTransition speed: Choose how fast to animate the transition between the previous slide and current slide.\r\n\r\n\r\nApply to All: Set the transition between all the slides.\r\nOn Mouse Click: Wait Until A Mouse Click To Move To The Next Slide.\r\nAutomatically After: Move To The Next Slide After A Certain No. Of Seconds\r\n\r\n','130','29/Jun/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
