 (593,7,'17','\r\n1.Selected lock cells\r\n2.Selected unlock cells\r\n3.format cells\r\n4.format coloumns\r\n5.format rows\r\n6.insert coloumns\r\n7.insert rows\r\n8.insert hyperlinks\r\n9.Delete rows\r\n10.Delete coloumns\r\n11.Sort\r\n12.Use auto filter\r\n13.Edit objects\r\n14.Edit scanner\'s\r\n15.use povit table reports\r\n','129','01/Jul/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (594,7,'18','\r\nIn excel sheet we can perform lot of built in functions. few of them are \r\nexplained as below.\\\\\\\\\\\r\n1.. copy:: to copy the excel sheet and place it before or after the required\r\nexcel steet.\\\\\\\\\\\\\r\n2... move:: to move the excel sheet to the place before or after the required\r\nsheet.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\r\n3...protect sheet:sheet protection options: we can protect the excel sheet by other users who may try to access the same sheet. this is done inorder to let the other users to perform only the authorised operations. This permission is given by use while protecting the excel sheet. \\\\\\\\\\\\\\ procedure: right click on the excel sheet.\\\\\\ there is a option called as protect sheet.\\\\\\\\ click on it and u will get protection options.\\\\\\ first of all set the password for protection so that only we can access.\\\\\\ laer click on the radio buttons telling which options are to be allowed by others.\\\\\\ click on ok and the sheet is protected.\r\n4.....rename: to rename the excel sheet\r\n5.....filter: to set filtering options to the excel sheet. by filtering we can hide the unwanted data and view only the priority data.\r\n\r\n','126','01/Jul/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (595,7,'15','HOME MENU: 1)\r\nClipboard 2)font\r\n3)paragraph\r\n4)Conditional formatting\r\n5)style\r\n6)Editing.\r\n\r\nparagraph:- \r\nOrientations: used to rotate a text in diagonale and verticle direction.\r\nLike Text Rotate up and Rotate down.\r\n\r\nSlyles:- \r\nConditional formatting:uses to mark the same value in color. \r\n\r\nHighlight cells rules: used to highlight the valules.   \r\n                       *Greater than, \r\n                       *Less than\r\n                       *in between\r\n                       *equal to \r\n                       *date occurring\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n','141','01/Jul/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
