 (612,7,'15','   1) HOME:\r\n   a)clipboard:\r\n   .)cut: This option is used to cut the selected data in office document.(ctrl+x)\r\n   .)copy: This option is used to copy the selected data from the office document.(ctrl+c)\r\n   .)paste: This option is used to paste the, cut or coppeid data to specific place. (ctrl+v)\r\n   b)font:\r\n   .)bold: This option is used to bold the selected words in the document.\r\n   .)italic: This option is used to chane the selected words style to italic.\r\n   .)under line: This option is used to underline the selected data.\r\n   .) increse font size: This option is used to increse the font size of selected data.\r\n   .) decrese font size: This option is used to decrese the font size of selected data.\r\n   .) font colour: This option is used to colour the selected words. \r\n   b) alignment:\r\n   .)Top aligne: this option is used to align the text to the top of the sheet.\r\n   .)middle aligne: This option is used to aligne the text to middle of sheet.\r\n   .)botom aligne: This option is used to aligne the text to the butom of sheet.\r\n   .)left aligne: This option is used to aline the text to the left of the sheet.\r\n   .)center aligne : This option is used to aligne the text to the center of the sheet.\r\n   .)right aligne: This option is used to aligne the text to the right of the sheet.\r\n   .)wrap text: Text appears on multiple lines in a cell.\r\n   .)merge and center: When you merge two or more adjacent horizontal or vertical cells, the cells become one large cell that is displayed across multiple columns or rows. The contents of one of the cells appear in the center of the merged cell.\r\n   c) styles:\r\n   .)conditional formating: Use a conditional format to help you visually explore and analyze data, detect critical issues, and identify patterns and trends.\r\n   .)format as table: quicly format selected cells and make them tables.\r\n   d) edditing: \r\n   .)auto sum:This option is used to calculate the mathema