 (685,7,'15','excel file having the options like home,insert,view,review etc. first one \r\nHOME-\r\n1)CLIPBOARD-a)cut b)copy c)paste\r\n2)FONT- a)bold b)italic c)underline and it also have option size of the fonts and color of the text.\r\n   3)ALIGNMENT-a)left b)right c)centre alignment d)justyfie\r\n   4)NUMBER-a)fraction b)decimal\r\n   5)STYLES-a)conditional formating b)table as format c)cell styles\r\n   \r\nINSERT-\r\n   1)Table-a)pivot table b)tables\r\n   2)illustration-a)picture b)cliparts c)shapes d)smartarts\r\n   3)chats-a)line b)pi c)cone d)circle\r\n   4)links -hyperlinks\r\n\r\n   PAGELAYOUT\r\n   1)themes-a)color b)\r\n   2)page setup- a)margins b)oriantation c)size\r\n   3)scale to fit\r\n   4)sheet options-a)gridline view\r\nVIEW\r\n\r\nPREVIEW\r\n\r\n','145','01/Jul/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science'),
 (686,7,'18','five built in operations \r\nmathematical and logical operations which can be perfofmed in the excel sheet cells\r\n1.sum: \r\nthe syntax for summing is \r\n=SUM(A1:C1)\r\nas shown above after choosing a cell, first we start with writing = sign which shows \r\nthere is a mathematical operation on that cell.\r\nthe summing opteration we have to choose the cells if it is from A1 to c1 we can write \r\na1:c1 in the braces it sums all the cell contents and puts in the cell where the \r\nformula is written\r\nsome other syntax\'es \r\n=sum(21,22,23,65,75)-which sums all the number written in the brace and returns the sum\r\n=sum(a1,d1,f1,z1)-slected cells are added.\r\n\r\n2.average:\r\nto find out the average of given numbers and cells\r\nsyntax:\r\n=average(a1:f1), =average(a1,b1,c1,f1,z1), =average(23,34,34,45,67,54).\r\n\r\n3. minimum\r\nreturns the minimum value in the given numbers\r\nsyntax:\r\n=min(a1:z1),=min(a1,b1,c1,d1).\r\n\r\n\r\n4.maximum:\r\nreturns the maximum value of the selected cells or numbers\r\n syntax:\r\n=max(a1:z1),=max(a1,b1,c1,d1).\r\n5.and \r\ndoes logical and operation like true or false. \r\nsyntax:\r\n=and(a1,b1),=and(1,0).\r\n6.or\r\nlogical or operation\r\nsyntax:\r\n=or(a1,b1),=or(1,0).\r\n7 if-\r\nif condition syntax:\r\n=if(condition,true ,false)\r\nas in the above syntax if condition opration first checks the condition\r\nif its true then executes first value else executes second command.\r\nexample: \r\n=if(a1>b1,\"greater\",\"lesser\")\r\n\r\n\r\n','135','01/Jul/2017','NC',0,'Computer Science');
